---
import PublicLayout from '../layouts/PublicLayout.astro';
---

<PublicLayout
  title="Terms of Service — Mnema"
  description="Mnema terms of service. Read about your rights and responsibilities when using Mnema."
  pathname="/terms"
>
  <section style="max-width: 720px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 80px 24px 120px;">
    <h1 style="font-size: 2rem; font-weight: 700; color: var(--text-primary); margin-bottom: 8px;">
      Terms of Service
    </h1>
    <p style="font-size: 13px; color: var(--text-tertiary); margin-bottom: 48px;">
      Last updated: May 26, 2026
    </p>

    <div style="color: var(--text-secondary); font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.75;">

      <h2 style="font-size: 1.1rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--text-primary); margin: 40px 0 12px;">
        1. Overview
      </h2>
      <p>
        These Terms of Service ("Terms") govern your access to and use of Mnema, a product operated by
        The Boring People ("we," "us," or "our"). By creating an account or using Mnema, you agree to
        be bound by these Terms. If you do not agree, do not use the service.
      </p>

      <h2 style="font-size: 1.1rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--text-primary); margin: 40px 0 12px;">
        2. Use of Service
      </h2>
      <p>
        Mnema is a knowledge management and workflow tool. You may use the service only for lawful
        purposes and in accordance with these Terms. You agree not to:
      </p>
      <ul style="padding-left: 20px; margin-top: 12px;">
        <li style="margin-bottom: 8px;">Use the service to transmit harmful, offensive, or illegal content.</li>
        <li style="margin-bottom: 8px;">Attempt to gain unauthorised access to any part of the service or its infrastructure.</li>
        <li style="margin-bottom: 8px;">Reverse-engineer, decompile, or disassemble any component of the service.</li>
        <li style="margin-bottom: 8px;">Resell or sublicense access to the service without our prior written consent.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 style="font-size: 1.1rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--text-primary); margin: 40px 0 12px;">
        3. Accounts and Workspaces
      </h2>
      <p>
        You are responsible for maintaining the confidentiality of your account credentials and for all
        activity that occurs under your account. You must notify us immediately of any unauthorised use.
        Each workspace you create is subject to the plan limits associated with your subscription.
      </p>

      <h2 style="font-size: 1.1rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--text-primary); margin: 40px 0 12px;">
        4. Intellectual Property
      </h2>
      <p>
        You retain all rights to the content you create in Mnema. By using the service, you grant us a
        limited, non-exclusive licence to store and display your content solely to provide the service
        to you. We do not claim ownership of your data.
      </p>
      <p style="margin-top: 12px;">
        The Mnema name, logo, and all related software are the intellectual property of The Boring People
        and may not be used without prior written permission.
      </p>

      <h2 style="font-size: 1.1rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--text-primary); margin: 40px 0 12px;">
        5. Payment and Billing
      </h2>
      <p>
        Paid plans are billed in advance on a monthly or annual basis. All fees are non-refundable
        except where required by law. We reserve the right to change pricing with 30 days' notice.
        Failure to pay may result in suspension or termination of your account.
      </p>

      <h2 style="font-size: 1.1rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--text-primary); margin: 40px 0 12px;">
        6. Termination
      </h2>
      <p>
        We may suspend or terminate your access to the service at any time if you violate these Terms
        or for any other reason at our sole discretion, with or without notice. You may cancel your
        account at any time from your account settings. Upon termination, your data will be retained
        for 30 days before permanent deletion.
      </p>

      <h2 style="font-size: 1.1rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--text-primary); margin: 40px 0 12px;">
        7. Disclaimer of Warranties
      </h2>
      <p>
        The service is provided "as is" and "as available" without warranties of any kind, either
        express or implied. We do not warrant that the service will be uninterrupted, error-free, or
        free of harmful components.
      </p>

      <h2 style="font-size: 1.1rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--text-primary); margin: 40px 0 12px;">
        8. Limitation of Liability
      </h2>
      <p>
        To the maximum extent permitted by applicable law, The Boring People shall not be liable for
        any indirect, incidental, special, consequential, or punitive damages arising from your use of
        the service. Our total liability shall not exceed the amount you paid us in the 12 months
        preceding the claim.
      </p>

      <h2 style="font-size: 1.1rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--text-primary); margin: 40px 0 12px;">
        9. Governing Law
      </h2>
      <p>
        These Terms are governed by the laws of India. Any disputes arising under these Terms shall be
        subject to the exclusive jurisdiction of the courts located in Bengaluru, Karnataka.
      </p>

      <h2 style="font-size: 1.1rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--text-primary); margin: 40px 0 12px;">
        10. Changes to Terms
      </h2>
      <p>
        We may update these Terms from time to time. We will notify you of material changes by email
        or by posting a notice in the application. Continued use after the effective date constitutes
        acceptance of the revised Terms.
      </p>

      <h2 style="font-size: 1.1rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--text-primary); margin: 40px 0 12px;">
        11. Contact
      </h2>
      <p>
        For questions about these Terms, contact us at{' '}
        <a href="mailto:hello@theboringpeople.in" style="color: var(--accent);">hello@theboringpeople.in</a>.
      </p>

    </div>
  </section>
</PublicLayout>
